1.) Create Dataset on TrueNAS Server
    a.) Go to Main Pool "RJ01NAS100_POOL"
    b.) Select the Three dots on the right side and select "Add Dataset"
    c.) Name PVE_BACKUP_Storage and PVE_VM_STORAGE
2.) Create NFS Share
    a.) Go to Sharing > NFS
    b.) Select "/mnt/RJ01NAS100_POOL/PVE_BACKUP_STORAGE" and "/mnt/RJ01NAS100_POOL/PVE_VM_STORAGE"
3.) Go to Proxmox > Datacenter > Storage
    a.) Add an NFS share
    b.) ID "Name", Server: "10.0.250.1"
    c.) Export: NFS Share
    d.) Select Content Stored Here
    e.) Allow for All Nodes

    
